---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms"
  description="General engagement terms for Del Security services and submission workflows."
  canonicalPath="/legal/terms"
>
  <article class="prose-shell card mx-auto max-w-4xl p-8">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-text">Terms</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-text-soft">Effective: February 2026</p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm">
      These terms provide a general framework for using this site and initiating contact with Del Security. Final obligations are defined in signed agreements such as NDA, MSA, or SOW.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Use of this site</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      This website provides informational content only. Submitting information through email does not create a contractual relationship by itself.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Authorized activity</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      Del Security only supports lawful and authorized security collaboration. Requests involving unauthorized intrusion, abusive exploitation, or illicit data are declined.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Engagement terms</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      Any paid or active engagement requires explicit scope, lawful purpose, and contractual documentation.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      All information and services are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, express or implied. Del Security disclaims all warranties, including but not limited to implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. Del Security does not guarantee that findings will be exhaustive or that all vulnerabilities will be identified.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Del Security shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising out of or related to the use of this site or any engagement, regardless of the theory of liability.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl">Updates</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
      These terms may be updated as operations evolve. Check the latest published version before initiating a new engagement.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
